<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">LAN Sharing (Optional)</h2><a id="user-content-lan-sharing-optional" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: LAN Sharing (Optional)" href="#lan-sharing-optional"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">By default, the proxy only listens on <code>127.0.0.1</code> (localhost), meaning only your computer can use it. To allow other devices on your local network (LAN) to use the proxy:</p>
<ol dir="auto">
<li>Set <code>"lan_sharing": true</code> in your <code>config.json</code></li>
<li>The proxy will automatically listen on all network interfaces (<code>0.0.0.0</code>)</li>
<li>The startup log will show your LAN IP addresses that other devices can connect to</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Example LAN configuration:</strong></p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-json notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="{
  &quot;lan_sharing&quot;: true,
  &quot;listen_host&quot;: &quot;0.0.0.0&quot;,
  &quot;listen_port&quot;: 8085
}"><pre>{
  <span class="pl-ent">"lan_sharing"</span>: <span class="pl-c1">true</span>,
  <span class="pl-ent">"listen_host"</span>: <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>0.0.0.0<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>,
  <span class="pl-ent">"listen_port"</span>: <span class="pl-c1">8085</span>
}</pre></div>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Security Warning:</strong> When LAN sharing is enabled, anyone on your local network can use your proxy. Ensure your network is trusted and consider additional security measures.</p>
<p dir="auto"><strong>On other devices:</strong> Configure them to use your computer's LAN IP (shown in the startup log) and port 8085 as the HTTP proxy.</p>
